  "body": "I have a search widget on a website -- it is a standalone react component, the user just puts the script on the site and the box is rendered.\r\n\r\nSee it at http://www.amihaiemil.com\r\n\r\nWhen a search is performed (e.g. \"test\"), the results are shown right below the input box. I want to close the search results if the user clicks outside of the widget (anywhere else on the page). But I don't know how to achieve this because the react component doesn't \"know\" anything about the rest of the page. And also, I cannot just hide the div with jquery, right? Because then I ruin React's virtual dom mechanism? ",
